node.text:
People want a voice in the decision-making! 📣 

As a leader, it is your duty to honor that, celebrate that, and intentionally practice that by allowing your team members to participate in those needle-moving conversations. When people feel like they have skin in the game, when they feel like they are actively contributing and a part of the creation, they will support you and your mission. 

You set the standard for what kind of team and communication will transpire. So be that positive example and influence for your team! Allow them a space to feel seen, heard, and appreciated for their ideas. 

That, my friends, is the defining duty and quality that separates a good leader from a GREAT one. 👏

#leadership #team #communication #voice #ideas #participation #leader #influence #personaldevelopment #teaching #wisdom #motivation #thebrendonshow #decision

node.text:
You might be getting a lot done, BUT…if you don’t feel aligned, you’re getting the WRONG things done. 

Listen — things are going to feel hard to you if they are not:

▶️ in alignment with your true passions and interests
▶️ bringing up curiosity and enthusiasm
▶️ filling you up when you’re doing it

So if you’re wondering why you just can’t get into something or you’ve lost your motivation, it’s not that something is wrong with you. Maybe something simply isn’t in alignment for you.

Think about it. Does that feel true?

Some #tuesdaythoughts for you, and cheering you on along the way. Your coach,
- Brendon.

#leadership #leadingothers #motivation #selfawareness #selfimprovement #selfgrowth #growthday #alignment #beinginalignment #passion #curiosity #enthusiasm

When you develop that trust — that is when the magic starts to happen, my friends. 💥

#thebrendonshow #trust #team #autonomy #leadership #motivation #wisdom

Are you FIGHTING for FOCUS, or just simply going through the motions with your team? 🤭

Whether it's the leader of a country, the CEO of a Fortune 500 company, or the parent leading their family, it's going to take persistence to really hammer in the values, vision, and expectations that need to be upheld.

So it may feel super repetitive, or like overkill, but you MUST repeat it to truly operationalize it long-term. 💥

What are some core values that you are trying to instill in your team as a leader? 👇

node.text:
"Brendon, you're CRAZY!" Just hear me out, okay? I know SO many couples who have all the love in the world, but without enthusiasm, without vibrancy, without spark, there will always be something missing. 🤭

It's time you really dig deep and take a closer look at your relationship. Are you and your partner *excited* about sharing and building a life together? Do you tackle your problems with real *enthusiasm* for the solution? 

I'm telling y'all, this is the secret ingredient to any successful relationship. I challenge you to lean into this idea. Show up for your partner. Bring aliveness and excitement to your relationship — for better or for worse. When you treat your joy and your conflict with the same enthusiasm, when you share a passion to build your futures together, when you face your problems head-on, THAT is when the magic starts. ❤️

#relationships #love #enthusiasm #vibrancy #relationshipadvice #marriage #partner #teamwork #conflict #growthday #lifecoach #aliveness #fridaymotivation

node.text:
The strongest relationships are built on encouragement. 🙌

The ability to encourage one another is SO vital. In research on relationships, we’ve found that happy couples tend to praise each other FIVE TIMES more than they complain or negate. 🤯

So with your partner, how often are you...
👉 Praising them?
👉 Encouraging them?
👉 Cheering them on?

What are the ways you can build more enthusiasm into your relationship? I know it sounds so simple, but watch how things change once you decide to prioritize this.

#wisdomwednesday #relationshipadvice #relationships #healthyrelationships #communication #healthycommunication #buildingtrust #enthusiasm #personalgrowth

node.text:
When someone is trapped in life, their ego won’t let them repair. Yup. Their ego holds onto bitterness and despair. It’s okay to be upset about things, that’s normal. But, remember — there are ways to repair and move on. Don’t let your ego get in the way of that happening.

#thursdaythoughts #relationshipadvice #ego #conflictresolution #motivation #inspiration #growthday #personaldevelopment #peace #harmony

node.title: The #1 Mindset Problem that Leads to Unhappiness

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Brendon Burchard on August 07, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Brendon Burchard @BrendonBurchard … I dropped jealously and comparison in my early 20s and honestly that made all the difference.'.

node.text:
Good time to reflect on your thoughts this last week, right?

A potential investor asked me how I’m so productive. First, I thanked my team. Second, I shared this quote. I just have a TON more mental energy than most people because I waste zero on thinking about how others have more or are more or how I should try to be like anyone else or copycat the other guy. 

People on a true path of purpose don’t waste mental energy on drama, comparison, jealousy, posturing outrage, or any hurtful thinking toward others. 

That mental energy instead goes to creativity, intention, passion, kindness, love, leadership. 

That’s the unfair advantage of personal development. 

Because we all start as rather unconscious children but we can grow into a consciousness of powerful self-reliance and soulful compassion and unity that makes life feel incredible. 

We can learn to recognize how lame, wasteful and hurtful our adolescent thoughts can be, and we can choose to be wildly more mindful, happy and loving.

People who do this work make self- improvement a way of life. When you’re ready, join us @growthday and download the GrowthDay app. Every day is a good day to grow.

Your coach,
Brendon.

#selfimprovement matters. #growthday #motivationalquotes

node.text:
Read this, and then READ it again!

How often are you letting doubt stop you? It can be a natural response—sometimes we don’t even recognize it—to shut down because we doubt ourselves.

But doubt just means there’s more for you to learn and grow into. Is that bad thing?

So whatever it is you’re doing and you face doubt, remind yourself of this line: Confidence is the belief in my ability to figure things out.

LET’S GO!!!! 

Tag a friend who needs this reminder 👇

#selfdoubt #overcomingobstacles #selfbelief #personaldevelopment #confidence #selfgrowth #selfimprovement #fridayfeeling #fridaymotivation #reels #inspiration #ambition

node.text:
We need to realize that most fear is just bad management of our minds. 🤭

If you’re letting fear stop you from moving forward, take a scroll through these 4 powerful tactics to help you beat back your fears. The things we need most in the face of fear is momentum and progress. These things quickly dissipate the fear that can take over our minds.

It’s okay to want to feel safe and protect yourself. That’s perfectly normal. Learning how to listen to that, then apply these tips intentionally, can really make a huge difference.

What’s your tip for overcoming fear? 👇 Share for someone reading the comments who’s curious!

#overcomingfear #fear #mindmanagement #emotionalmanagement #fearlessmotivation #selfawareness #personalgrowth #lifecoaching #lifecoach #momentum #progess #teachingideas

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Brendon Burchard on August 05, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'How to BEAT BACK YOUR FEARS @brendonburchard'.

Photo by Brendon Burchard on August 05, 2021. May be an image of text that says '01 FOR YOUR PROGRESS STOP BLAMING FEAR Stop thinking the reason you are not getting ahead is because of fear. It's a grand lie we tell ourselves We need to realize that most fear is just bad management of our minds. Fear is usually not the thing holding people back. What's usually holding them back is a lack of connection with something more important than fear. @brendonburchard'.

Photo by Brendon Burchard on August 05, 2021. May be an image of text that says '02 CONFRONT YOUR FEARS ON PAPER Think of the dream you have and any reason you've been stopping. Write down why. What would you have to go learn, do, or ask for in order to overcome that fear or that challenge? Sometimes, the biggest breakthrough for people's lives is when they write stuff down. @brendonburchard'.

Photo by Brendon Burchard on August 05, 2021. May be an image of text that says '03 TAKE DAILY ACTION Fear tends to dissipate with daily action. Accomplish three goals a day It could even be something as simple as taking a shower. Find three things that you can do every day that's appropriate for where you're at in your life and just do them because momentum beats the pants out of fear. @brendonburchard'.

Photo by Brendon Burchard on August 05, 2021. May be an image of text that says '04 YOUR CRAZY GOALS ASPIRE TO REACH Write down three big crazy things you want in life. Then, write the fear you'd have if you chase or accomplish them. The more you think about your fears, the more you realize they're silly and those worst case scenarios almost never happen. And the more you realize you deserve something beyond them, the more you see that you don't deserve to live a life trapped by fear. @brendonburchard'.

Photo by Brendon Burchard on August 05, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TODAY'S COPING POINTS: 1. No matter the emotion, breathe through it. 2. See and sense the scene you're in now; don't go into tunnel vision and zoom in on one thing from the past to be upset about. 3. Affirm in your mind that you're ok, and you'll move through this well because you are choosing to do so. 4. Set an intention: How will you define this and how would your best self act from here? 5. Be patient and be consistent and honor yourself and your future. @BrendonBurchard'.

node.text:
First… breathe.

I would have thought the pandemic would force us all to learn how to cope with our emotions and uncertainty better. 

I sense that happened for our community—people into personal development—but not as broadly as one would have imagined. 

If anything, consumption of hyperbolic social media seems to have only amplified people’s unconscious desires to hyper rationalize their own ego, outrage, fears, impatience, and sense of righteousness disconnected from social acuity or benefit.

What can be done?

Both children and adults need to be inspired to learn about their own emotions, mental health and consciousness. 

An easy entry point is learning to cope and calm themselves. That’s a gate to personal growth too.

What I’m proud of at @growthday is that our app gives people a daily touchpoint of personal development topics and experts. The more we pause to think about our lives and how we feel and how we want to be, connect, contribute and grow, the more our sense of consciousness, intention and social connection expands. Then we make better decisions. And we become happier and kinder over time.

Funny how all that can begin with such simple things like breathing and coping better in the moment. 

Cheering you on today no matter what you’re facing.

Your coach,
Brendon.

#mentalhealth #coaching #calm #personaldevelopment #growthday #inspiration

People want a voice in the decision-making! 📣 

As a leader, it is your duty to honor that, celebrate that, and intentionally practice that by allowing your team members to participate in those needle-moving conversations. When people feel like they have skin in the game, when they feel like they are actively contributing and a part of the creation, they will support you and your mission. 

You set the standard for what kind of team and communication will transpire. So be that positive example and influence for your team! Allow them a space to feel seen, heard, and appreciated for their ideas. 

That, my friends, is the defining duty and quality that separates a good leader from a GREAT one. 👏

#leadership #team #communication #voice #ideas #participation #leader #influence #personaldevelopment #teaching #wisdom #motivation #thebrendonshow #decision

The past is the past man. The future holds good things for you but you must be HUNGRY for it and WORK for it. We all know this. So revisit your goals right now. Get off socials. Go do the work. 

Demonstrate desire and commitment long enough and the universe hears the knocks and opens the doors.

Your coach,
Brendon.

node.text:
No filter on this background photo—I took it yesterday. So gorgeous. Speaking of this photo…

Few people know that for the first 10 YEARS I was Facebook, most of the photos behind my quotes were photos I had taken. Then, I’d type the quotes over the photo in an app. Not rocket science, but that was 2007. And the thing is, I did that 2-4 times per day, everyday, for a decade. That’s a lot of photos and writing. 

So, when people look at my 5mil fans on Facebook, they think it happened overnight. But back then it was just me, and I was just clear that Facebook was going to be a place for my photos and art not my ego. 

Today, people don’t even think about the photos behind quotes bc quotes became a thing. 

But man that original art really made the difference in those years.

Today, with all my pages like this one and @growthday and all my companies, I have help. But the idea is still the same - deliver some goodness and inspiration every single day 2-4 times. Each post adds up over time and suddenly you have something that matters.

On today’s Daily Fire in the GrowthDay app, I talked about how transformation takes time. I hope you’ll listen.

One day at a time my friend. 

Your coach, 
Brendon.

#motivationalquotes #transformationtuesday #lifecoaching
